The paper analyzes the choices people make about what information to propagate on citation networks, which involves social communication and information dissemination. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Social and Information Retrieval (cs.SI) or Social Network Analysis and Graph Algorithms (cs.SD) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the dissemination of scholarly knowledge and adoption of innovation, which could fall under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also mentions patents and legal opinions, which could relate to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
